        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 5:23PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 523 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles west of Agate, or 23 miles northwest of Limon, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Deer Trail, Agate and Cottonwood Valley.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
